truthy value
	
	true
	all other numbers expect 0
	'str' --> not empty string
	{}
	[]

falsy value
	
	false
	0
	''
	undefined
	null


logical and 

	--> exp1 && exp2

	--> exp1 is returned if exp1 is a falsy value, else exp2 is returned

logical or

	--> exp1 || exp2

	--> exp1 is returned if exp1 is a truthy value, else exp2 is returned

isArray() --> method to identify if the varible is an array

length --> it will let you know whats the length of the array

push() --> adding the item at the end of the array

pop() --> remove the item from the end of array

unshift() --> add an item in the starting of the array

shift() --> remove the item for the starting of the array

indexOf(item) -- first occurance of specific value

lastIndexOf(item) -- last occurance of specific value.